{title: Answer To Rainbow At Midnight}
{artist: Ernest Tubb}
{composer: Written by Warren Michael Defever}

[G]I saw a rainbow at [C]midnight
Way [G]out on the ocean so [D7]blue
And [G]there was your face in this [C]rainbow
[G]Guiding me [D7]back home to [G]you
All through the war I was [C]praying
For the [G]day that you’d be by my [D7]side
But [G]now all my dreams have been [C]shattered
It [G]seems that my [D7]rainbow has [G]lied

For when I knocked on your [C]door dear
They [G]said with a new love you’d [D7]gone
And [G]that you two were so [C]happy
And for [G]me to just [D7]leave you [G]alone
Oh how my poor heart did [C]break dear
For I [G]suffered so much for so [D7]long
And [G]you knew just how much I [C]loved you
Oh [G]how could you [D7]treat me so [G]wrong
Now as I gaze at your [C]heaven
It [G]seems I just can’t bear the [D7]pain
Yet [G]somehow each night I keep [C]searching
For a [G]rainbow I’ll [D7]never see [G]again